Lagos State Government, on Thursday, announced the arrest of a wife beater, Afobaje Maiyegun. Gboyega Akosile, Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, gave the update on Twitter. He confirmed that the Lagos Domestic and Sexual Violence Response Team (DSVRT) apprehended the man. In a viral Facebook post, Afobaje Maiyegun, boasted that he beat up his wife. He posted a photo of her bloody face and declared he was “waiting for the police” to come and arrest him. Akosile said the DSVRT reached out to ACP Gbolahan Odugbemi, Police Commander in Area J, who took an immediate action. “Preliminary investigation conducted revealed that this is not the first time the said Mr. Maiyegun would perpetrate such a dastardly act. “A partner NGO, @HerfessionsApp, was on ground to assist with the investigation. The case is set to be charged to court on Friday, 15th May, 2020”, he tweeted. Akosile reiterated that Governor Babajide Sanwo-Old had declared zero tolerance to sexual and gender Based violence in Lagos. The CPS warned that perpetrators will face the full weight of the law.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-792128" src=https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/IMG_20200514_092251.jpg alt width=474 height=735 srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/IMG_20200514_092251.jpg 474w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/IMG_20200514_092251-193x300.jpg 193w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px">